  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age &gt; 18 years

          -  Patients undergoing thyroidectomy

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients who had received antiemetic therapy within 48 hours before surgery

          -  Patients with depression

          -  Chronic pain disorder

          -  Insulin-dependent diabetes mellitus

          -  History of severe and/or repeated PONV after previous minor surgery, that led to
             change from standard anesthetic protocol

          -  Pregnancy

          -  Age &lt; 18 years

          -  Patients who had known malignant disease or had undergone previous thyroid or neck
             surgery
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
